cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper proposes a connectionist-inspired kernel machine model for learning distributed and hierarchical representations, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also compares the proposed model with state-of-the-art multiple kernel learning algorithms and popular deep architectures, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SD). Among these sub-categories, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely ones as they are directly related to the proposed model and its applications.
